### Spring Boot Authentication System - Esempi di Richieste HTTP

### 1. Registrazione Utente
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "mrossi",
  "email": "mario.rossi@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Mario",
  "lastName": "Rossi",
  "phoneNumber": "+39123456789"
}

### 2. Login
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "mrossi",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Login con Email
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "mario.rossi@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Refresh Token
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "inserisci-qui-il-refresh-token"
}

### 5. Get Current User (Protetto)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer inserisci-qui-l-access-token

### 6. Update Profile (Protetto)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/users/me
Authorization: Bearer inserisci-qui-l-access-token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Mario Giovanni",
  "lastName": "Rossi",
  "phoneNumber": "+39987654321",
  "email": "mario.rossi@newmail.com"
}

### 7. Logout
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "inserisci-qui-il-refresh-token"
}

### NOTA: Sostituisci i token con quelli ricevuti dalle risposte precedenti
